This paper deals with the problem of providing Internet access to rural areas using LTE-A networks operating in TV white space. This topic is closely related to the field of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and communication and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the issue of spectrum sharing, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves the use of graph theory and optimization algorithms, which are relevant to the field of computer science and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of improving system fairness, which is related to the field of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
